    <item rdf:about="https://lwn.net/Articles/844257/rss">
      <title>An unpleasant sudo vulnerability</title>
      <link>https://lwn.net/Articles/844257/</link>
      <dc:date>2021-01-28T00:15:19+00:00</dc:date>
      <dc:creator>corbet</dc:creator>
      <description>
      It would appear that &quot;sudo&quot; has a buffer-overflow vulnerability that allows
any local user to gain root privileges, whether or not they are in the
&lt;tt&gt;sudoers&lt;/tt&gt; file.  It has been there since 2011.  See &lt;a
href=&quot;https://lwn.net/ml/oss-security/20210126181453.GA4184@localhost.localdomain/&quot;&gt;this
advisory&lt;/a&gt; for details, but perhaps run an update first.
      
      </description>
    </item>
